            <a href="javascript:void(0)">
              <h3 class="title">Thetaboard</h3>
            </a>
            <p class="description">
              What is Thetaboard?
            </p>
          </div>
          <p></p>
          <div class="card-description">
            <p>
              Thetaboard's mission is to become the central place for any Theta enthusiast. <br>
              We want to bring value to the Theta ecosystem by providing functionalities
              that either simplifies access to information about Theta, or enrich the ecosystem.<br>

              We currently have:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li><a href="#dashboard">A Dashboard</a></li>
              <li><a href="#wallet">A Wallet</a></li>
              <li><a href="#domain">Domains</a></li>
              <li><a href="#guardian">Public Guardian Node</a></li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              Thetaboard is an open source project hosted on <a
                    target="_blank" href="https://github.com/momohuri/thetaboard">github</a>.
              And we encourage people to deploy their own instance of Thetaboard using the easy instructions so they can
              have their own Guardian Node. <br>
              This project is primarily developed and maintained by Maurin Lenglart and Adrien Vinches.<br>
              We can be contacted for support or suggestions on <a target="_blank" href="https://discord.gg/SGUtY7zBU3"> discord</a>.
              <br>
              If you like the project you can make a donation at  {{donation/donation}}
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row" id="dashboard">
    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12">
      <div class="card card-user">
        <div class="card-body">
          <p class="card-text">
          </p>
          <div class="author">
            <div class="block block-one"></div>
            <div class="block block-two"></div>
            <div class="block block-three"></div>
            <div class="block block-four"></div>
            <a href="javascript:void(0)">
              <h3 class="title">Dashboard</h3>
            </a>
            <p class="description">
              What is the Dashboard page?
            </p>
          </div>
          <p></p>
          <div class="card-description">
            <p>
              The Dashboard page exists to report information about Theta and Tfuel price evolution and wallets.<br>
              To get information about a specific wallet, it possible to either search for it
              by address or <a href="#domain">domain</a> by clicking on the search bar,
              or connect your wallet using the <a
                    target="_blank" href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/Theta-wallet/ckelpdlfgochnkdgikcgbimdcfgpkhgk">official
              Theta Wallet extension</a>.<br>
              It currently has 5 widgets:
            </p>
            <br/>
            <ul class="no-list-deco">
              <li><b>Theta & Tfuel line chart: </b><br/>This widget provides historic price information for both crypto
                currencies. It can be filtered by year, month, or week.
              </li><br/>
              <li><b> Wallet Composition: </b><br/>It displays a pie chart, representing all the Theta and Tfuel held by
                the wallet with the
                composition in $ value.
              </li><br/>
              <li><b> Theta & Tfuel price: </b><br/>These two widgets provide current Theta and Tfuel price,
                the price/percentage change from the last 24 hours/last 7 days, followed by the market cap and the last 24 hours volume.
              </li><br/>
              <li><b> Guardian Node Reward Forecast: </b><br/>Staking Theta on a Guardian Node gives TFuel as rewards. There
                is a minimum of {{format-number 1000}} Theta requirement in order to stake. When inputing an amount of Theta staked, the widget will
                forecast how many Tfuel will be rewarded by day/month/year.
              </li><br/>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
